00:57:20,840 --> 00:57:22,200
So let's look at it.

709
00:57:22,520 --> 00:57:23,801
184.

710
00:57:23,801 --> 00:57:33,321
Zosima's making this big speech about guilt at the second sentence or third sentence of the second paragraph, 184.

711
00:57:34,040 --> 00:57:39,400
Because we have come here and shut ourselves within these walls, we are no holier than those that are outside.

712
00:57:39,400 --> 00:57:48,521
On the contrary, for the very fact of coming here, each of us has confessed to himself that he is worse than others, worse than all the men on earth.

713
00:57:48,520 --> 00:58:01,880
And skipping a little, when he realizes that he's not only worse than others, but he's responsible to all men for all and everything, for all human sins, national and individual, only then can the aim of our seclusion be attained.

714
00:58:01,880 --> 00:58:14,840
For know, dear ones, that every one of us is undoubtedly responsible for all men and everything on earth, not merely through the general sinfulness of creation, but each one personally for all mankind and every individual man.

715
00:58:15,161 --> 00:58:17,880
Now, that's a very strange speech.

716
00:58:17,960 --> 00:58:25,560
Took me a long time to sort of free myself from it because the critics all say, isn't that interesting?

717
00:58:25,560 --> 00:58:26,200
Wonderful.

718
00:58:26,201 --> 00:58:28,520
What an amazing character Father Zosima is.

719
00:58:28,520 --> 00:58:30,960
He feels responsible for all the evil in the world.

720
00:58:31,121 --> 00:58:37,281
We're guilty for it individually and personally, for all of it everywhere.

721
00:58:37,681 --> 00:58:39,441
But that's just crazy.

722
00:58:39,440 --> 00:58:43,360
I mean, you can't, and I can't, feel guilty for the...

723
00:58:44,480 --> 00:58:53,920
the thirsty people in the desert or the, I don't know, some Chinese family that's malfunctioning and so forth.

724
00:58:53,920 --> 00:58:58,481
We can't even feel guilty for all the families in Berkeley that are malfunctioning.

725
00:58:58,480 --> 00:59:01,281
I mean, it's just impossible to do that.

726
00:59:01,281 --> 00:59:10,641
And this story that Zosima's telling, which he's telling so well and so moving, and he's such a nice man, you wonder, what does Dostoevsky think about that?

727
00:59:10,641 --> 00:59:22,721
Well, Dostoevsky doesn't ever sort of say that he thinks this is a crazy view, but he shows you that that's not the right view.

728
00:59:22,721 --> 00:59:27,520
And that you get this crazy view if you withdraw into the monastery.

729
00:59:27,520 --> 00:59:29,601
That is really what they're guilty of.

730
00:59:29,601 --> 00:59:32,801
Zosima says we're all guilty because we come here.

731
00:59:35,281 --> 00:59:43,281
But when they come there and withdraw from the world, they can't really deal with all the evil in the world.

732
00:59:43,761 --> 00:59:54,321
Their guilt is that they can feel guilty about everything, but it doesn't make any sense because they're not really guilty in any sensible way.

733
00:59:54,321 --> 00:59:57,840
And if they're staying in the monastery, they can't do anything about it.

734
00:59:57,840 --> 01:00:04,560
So I think we're supposed to think that that is equally wrong.

735
01:00:04,560 --> 01:00:10,561
It's as wrong as Yvonne thinking that you should get out of the world and give back your ticket.

736
01:00:10,560 --> 01:00:16,200
There's a way in which Zosima gets out of the world and goes into the monastery, which is wrong.

737
01:00:16,520 --> 01:00:23,401
Yvonne does it being very righteous, saying, you know, any decent person should get out of the world and I'm leaving.

738
01:00:23,400 --> 01:00:25,720
Zosima has an opposite view.

739
01:00:25,721 --> 01:00:33,321
He gets out of the world and feels very guilty for doing it and guilty for all the evil in the world, but he doesn't do anything about it.

740
01:00:33,480 --> 01:00:38,681
That's what you all see, is that can't be the right attitude.

741
01:00:38,681 --> 01:00:54,840
He assumes responsibility for all the evil in the world, but and he wants, he feels that he's, he doesn't ask how he can forgive all the bad people.

742
01:00:54,840 --> 01:01:00,840
He asks, who could forgive all those bad people, Yvonne asks at one point.

