766
01:02:39,360 --> 01:02:47,041
So again, Smerzhikov is copying Yvonne, and they're taking this, we're not responsible for any of the evil in the world story.

767
01:02:47,040 --> 01:02:49,681
And Zosima is taking the opposite view.

768
01:02:49,681 --> 01:02:53,840
I'm responsible, me, Zosima, for all the evil in the world.

769
01:02:54,161 --> 01:03:04,001
And I think the answer is supposed to be that Zosima's wrong view comes from stepping out of the world.

770
01:03:04,000 --> 01:03:11,041
It's not the suicide kind of giving up, but he sort of gives back his ticket when he goes into the monastery.

771
01:03:11,040 --> 01:03:15,601
And so that he isn't in any particular situation.

772
01:03:16,321 --> 01:03:20,000
It's not a case of philosophical detachment like Yvonne.

773
01:03:20,000 --> 01:03:22,641
It's sort of monastery detachment.

